The paper discusses the integration of a type-based synthesis algorithm and its IDE with a logistics lab environment consisting of Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS) such as robots and drones. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the challenges of coping with large spaces of software, hardware, and problem-specific solution variability, which could indicate a connection to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of formal methods in the development of CPS-enabled industrial environments, which could suggest a connection to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
